1) Download desired Splunk UF for Windows MSI to static/ folder. 

2) Edit bin/upgrade-wrap.cmd with splunk home directory.

3) Edit bin/upgrade.ps1, set the variable $splunkInstaller value to MSI filename

4) Edit bin/upgrade.ps1, incase splunk service is running with Service domain account, update logon/password accordingly.

5) Update the inputs.conf, as the scripts generate the upgrade.log provide valid directory location.

Note: Do not uncomment the LOGON_USERNAME/PASSWORD, if splunk is installed with 'local system' account.
